We Can't Dance is the fourteenth studio album from the English rock band Genesis
released in November 1991 on Virgin Records in the United Kingdom and Atlantic
Records in the United States. It is their last album recorded with drummer and
lead singer Phil Collins before his departure in 1996 to pursue solo projects
Production began after a four-year period of inactivity from the group, following
the commercial success of Invisible Touch (1986) and its tour.
